# Prefab Editor (dev-only)

Dev server port **4173** (`npm run dev`). Open via title-screen **Editor** or `?boot=editor`. Dev servers are normally already running — do not start `npm run dev` unless asked.

## Architecture

```
react/main.tsx → EditorApp (React shell, Fast Refresh)
document.ts (EditorStore) → serialize.ts → world/prefabs/schema.ts
react/panels/* (React UI)   panels/*_logic.ts + ImperativeHost leftovers
component_actions.ts        world/prefabs/component_registry.ts
glb_binding.ts              render/editor/viewport.ts (Three.js, imperative)
                            render/prefabs/prefab_renderer.ts (runtime)
```

- **React UI** lives in `src/editor/react/` (shell, Project, Hierarchy, Toolbar, Inspector chrome, Material Manager).
- **EditorStore** and serialize stay framework-agnostic in `src/editor/`.
- **Imperative hosts**: prefab viewport, base-characters stage, planet/system/menu tab editors, and dense inspector component field builders (`inspector_component_fields_dom.ts` / `particle_fields.ts`).
- HMR: Fast Refresh for React panels; soft remount + sessionStorage snapshot for store/tab/selection; CSS hot-swaps via `styles.ts`. Prefab/planet/system JSON stays on Vite `watch.ignored`.

Editor logic stays in `src/editor/`. Three.js viewport in `src/render/editor/`. Prefab JSON contract in `world/prefabs/`.

## Selection model

- **Entity selection** — LMB viewport or hierarchy row. Clears GLB sub-selection.
- **GLB sub-selection** — viewport drill-down (LMB same spot), or click a node in the hierarchy GLB tree. Required for node-scoped inspector fields and **Add Component to Node**.
- GLB overrides persist by **node name**, not UUID. Resolve via `store.getGlbNodeName()` before save.

## Adding components (`component_actions.ts`)

| Entry point | Path |
|-------------|------|
| Inspector combobox | `react/panels/InspectorPanel.tsx` |
| RMB entity → Components | `react/panels/HierarchyPanel.tsx` |
| RMB GLB node → Add Component to Node | `HierarchyPanel.tsx` / `viewport.ts` |

**Where data lands:**
- `marker: true` on a visual entity → **child empty** at node position; set `glbAnchor`.
- Collider + GLB sub-selection → `glbNodeTransforms[].components` (node override).
- Otherwise → `entity.components`.

Palette filtered by prefab **kind**; **singleton** types are once-per-document.

## GLB hierarchy binding (critical)

GLB nodes are **not** entities. Child empties/markers nest under a GLB node in the outliner only when bound:

- **Preferred:** `entity.glbAnchor = "<exact GLB node name>"` (serialized on `PrefabEntity.glbAnchor`).
- **Legacy:** `Name (GlbNodeName)` suffix — parsed by `glbAnchorFromEntityName()` in `glb_binding.ts`.
- **Never** use regex `\(([^)]+)\)$` for binding — breaks names like `Foo_(3)`.

Hierarchy uses `entityTargetsGlbNode` / `entityBoundToAnyGlbNode` from `glb_binding.ts`. When adding from a GLB context menu, always set `glbAnchor` on the new entity.

